  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Matcha Barista",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Description:</strong></u></p>\n<p><strong>• Customer Service</strong> : Greet and assist customers with a friendly attitude, attending to customers' queries and concerns.</p>\n<p><strong>• Customer Engagement &amp; Satisfaction</strong> : Engage in meaningful conversations with customers on concept, products and tea knowledge. Ensure every customer leaves satisfied with their experience.</p>\n<p><strong>• Beverage Preparation</strong> : Prepare, plate and serve food and drinks, following recipes and quality standards.</p>\n<p><strong>• Opening &amp; closing of outlets</strong></p>\n<p><strong>• Inventory</strong> : receiving and checking of inventory and perishables.</p>\n<p><strong>• Cleanliness &amp; Organization</strong> : Maintain a clean and organized work station, including prepping ingredients, sanitizing surfaces, and keeping the cafe area tidy.</p>\n<p><strong>• Team Collaboration</strong> : Work closely with other crew members to ensure smooth operations and a positive work environment.</p>\n<p><strong>• Reports to</strong> : Outlet Manager</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Requirement :</strong></u></p>\n<p>• Experience and interest in F&amp;B</p>\n<p>• Passion for tea, including acquiring and sharing of tea knowledge</p>\n<p>• Able to work weekends &amp; public holidays</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Skills &amp; Abilities:</strong></u></p>\n<p>• Well-groomed with good communication and interpersonal skills</p>\n<p>• Fluent in English</p>\n<p>• Proactive and reliable, able to adapt and learn quickly</p>\n<p>• Ability to withstand stress and work well under pressure</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><u><strong>Other job details:</strong></u></p>\n<p>• 5 day work week, no split shifts</p>\n<p>• Medical claim system</p>\n<p>• 14 days of annual leave (upon completion of probation period, prorated)</p>\n<p>• Individual welfare fund (upon completion of probation period, prorated)</p>",
